    Woman with a Parasol – Madame Monet and Her Son (1875) is also often regarded as one of his more well-known and appreciated works.     Search for: Where are most Monet paintings?
    How many paintings did Monet paint?
    Monet's "Series paintings" are well known and notable, and include Haystacks, Water Lilies, Rouen Cathedrals, Houses of Parliament, Charing Cross Bridge, and Poplar Trees. His prodigious output of nearly 2000 paintings was catalogued by Daniel Wildenstein.

    About

    Description

    Oscar-Claude Monet was a French painter and founder of impressionist painting who is seen as a key precursor to modernism, especially in his attempts to paint nature as he perceived it. Wikipedia
    Born: November 14, 1840, Rue Laffitte, Paris, France
    Died: December 5, 1926 (age 86 years), Giverny, France
    Influenced by: Édouard Manet, Pierre-Auguste Renoir, MORE
    Periods: Impressionism, Modern art
    Children: Michel Monet, Jean Monet
    Influenced: Vincent van Gogh, Pierre-Auguste Renoir, MORE
